{
  "texts": [
    "For example:• Ambiguous Instruction: \"Clean up the room.\"",
    "C. Embodied Knowledge Graph (EKG)The Embodied Knowledge Graph (EKG) is a structured representation of the robot's environment, implemented using Neo4j's graph database architecture [68].",
    "It encapsulates spatial, physical, temporal, and task-specific parameters, enabling the robot to reason about its environment and validate task plans against real-time data.",
    "The EKG is formally defined as:EKG = {(v i, r j, v k) | v i, v k ∈ V, r j ∈ R},where:• v i, v k: Vertices representing entities (e.g., objects, locations, tasks), • r j: Relationships between entities (e.g., \"located on,\" \"part of\").",
    "1) Real-Time Updates for EKG: The EKG integrates both synchronous and asynchronous updates to balance safety and efficiency."
  ]
}